column26:
The footnote on p. 131 says that a plant in China is not included in 2016 and 2017 because: "as some utilities and some
general systems are still shared with other activities that are not controlled by Brembo". Is this problematic so that we need to label 2016 and 2017 as wrong? Other than that the extraction was perfectly correct
column38: We tend to accept the 2016 and 2017 values. However we need to decide what missing quantities are acceptable. Also there might be an issue with the comparibilty over time in a case like this. Problem with varying page numbers.
column52: The values without the plant should be ok, as we assume this choice is  in line with the control approach under GHG Protocol

[...] The amount of CO₂ emitted from over overseas production facilities in 2019 was 9,137 t-CO₂. (p. 45). P. 44 nennt zusätzlich die Zahl 19 512. Tabelle auf S. 56 nennt weitere, andere Zahlen.
